Sentencas: Zinc-doped barium strontium cobalt ferrite (Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.2-xZnxFe0.8O3-delta (BSCZF), x = 0, 0.05, 0.1, 0.15, 0.2) powders with various proportions of zinc were prepared using the ethylenediamine tetraacetic acid (EDTA)-citrate method with repeated ball-milling and calcining.
Titulo: Electrochemical behavior of Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.2-xZnxFe0.8O3-δ (X=0-0.2) perovskite oxides for the cathode of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: They were then evaluated as cathode materials for solid oxide fuel cells at intermediate temperatures (IT-SOFCs) using XRD, H-2-TPR, SEM, and electrochemical tests.
Titulo: Electrochemical behavior of Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.2-xZnxFe0.8O3-δ (X=0-0.2) perovskite oxides for the cathode of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: By varying the zinc doping (x) from zero to 0.2 (as a substitution for cobalt which ranged from zero to 100%), it was found that the lowest doping of 0.05 (BSCZF05) resulted in the highest electrical conductivity of 30.7 S cm(-1) at 500 degrees C.
Titulo: Electrochemical behavior of Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.2-xZnxFe0.8O3-δ (X=0-0.2) perovskite oxides for the cathode of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The polarization resistances of BSCZFO5 sintered at 950 degrees C were 0.15 Omega cm(2), 0.28 cm(2) and 0.59 cm(2) at 700 degrees C, 650 degrees C and 600 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: Electrochemical behavior of Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.2-xZnxFe0.8O3-δ (X=0-0.2) perovskite oxides for the cathode of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The resistance decreased further by about 30% when Sm0.2Ce0.8O2-delta (SDC) electrolyte particles were incorporated and the sintering temperature was increased to 1000 degrees C.
Titulo: Electrochemical behavior of Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.2-xZnxFe0.8O3-δ (X=0-0.2) perovskite oxides for the cathode of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Compared to BSCF without zinc, BSCZF experienced the lowest decrease in electrochemical properties when the sintering temperature was increased from 950 degrees C to 1000 degrees C.
Titulo: Electrochemical behavior of Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.2-xZnxFe0.8O3-δ (X=0-0.2) perovskite oxides for the cathode of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: This decrease was due to an increase in thermal stability and a minimization in the loss of some cobalt cations without a decrease in the electrical conductivity.
Titulo: Electrochemical behavior of Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.2-xZnxFe0.8O3-δ (X=0-0.2) perovskite oxides for the cathode of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Using a composite cathode of BSCZFO5 and 30 wt.% of SDC, button cells composed of an Ni-SDC support with a 30 mu m dense SDC membrane exhibited a maximum power density of 605 mW cm(-2) at 700 degrees C. Copyright (C) 2011, Hydrogen Energy Publications, LLC.
